Aren't they almost the same thing? One with concrete numbers and the other one with variables.

----

It highly depends on whether or not you are comfortable with formal proofs. If you know how to write a formal inductive proof or a different proof by contradiction, then you should be fine with taking 110; otherwise, take CS 70/Math55 first.


As for the non-proof material, EE16A is enough preparation. Math 110 is actually valid as a class on its own, without a Math54/EE16A prereq, since the class will go over everything again and reteach the basics.

I would say that CS 70 (or Math 55) is better suited as preparation for the proof-focused format of 110.
